style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Item 7.01 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Regulation FD Disclosure</font></div><div style="line-
height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;padding-top:0px;text-align:justify;font-
size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">CrossAmerica 
Partners LP (NYSE: CAPL) ("CrossAmerica" or the "Partnership"), on August 22, 
2016 announced that the owner of its General Partner, CST Brands, Inc. (NYSE: 
CST) has entered into a definitive merger agreement with Alimentation Couche-
Tard Inc. (TSX: ATD.A ATD.B) ("Couche-Tard"). Under the terms of the agreement, 
Couche-Tard will, through its acquisition of CST, acquire CST&#8217;s interest 
in the General Partner and CST&#8217;s approximately 19% limited partner 
interest in CrossAmerica as well as all of the Incentive Distribution Rights 
("IDRs"). The transaction has been unanimously approved by the Board of 
Directors of CST and Couche-Tard and is subject to the approval of CST&#8217;s 
shareholders and the receipt of regulatory approvals. The transaction is 
currently expected to close early calendar year 2017. </font></div><div
style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;padding-top:0px;text-
align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;">The press release is furnished as Exhibit 99.1 
hereto.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;padding-
top:0px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-
family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">On August 22, 2016, the Partnership released a 
presentation regarding the transaction.  The slide presentation will be 
available on the Webcasts &amp; Presentations page of the Partnership&#8217;s 
website at www.crossamericapartners.com.  The slide presentation is furnished as
Exhibit 99.2 hereto and is incorporated herein by reference.</font></div><div 
style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:8px;padding-top:12px;text-
align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;">The information in this Current Report is being furnished pursuant 
to Regulation FD.  The information in Item 7.01 and Exhibits 99.1 and 99.2 of 
Item 9.01 of this report, according to general instruction B.2., shall not be 
deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for the purposes of Section 18 of the Securities 
Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise 
subject to the liabilities of that Section.  The information in this Current 
Report shall not be incorporated by reference into any registration statement 
pursuant to the Securities Act of 1933, as amended.  By filing this report on 
Form 8-K and furnishing this information, the Partnership makes no admission as 
to the materiality of any information in this report that the Partnership
 chooses to disclose solely because of Regulation FD.</font></div><div><a 
name="sFA8AAE8A29FA3F75374BB25DD0C7D277"></a></div><div style="line-

<body style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">
<div><a name="saf7dcf9b687545cfb3bf62a1be6b86b8"></a></div><div><div 
style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><div><br></div><div style="line-
height:174%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-
family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-
height:174%;padding-bottom:21px;padding-top:12px;text-align:center;"><img 
src="caplogo1.jpg" style="height:126px;width:162px;"></div><div style="line-
height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font 
style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Owner of 
CrossAmerica Partners LP&#8217;s General Partner, CST Brands, Inc., Enters into 
Merger Agreement with Alimentation Couche-Tard Inc.</font></div><div 
style="line-height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-align:justify;font-
size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Allentown, PA, 
August 22, 2016 - CrossAmerica Partners LP (NYSE: CAPL) ("CrossAmerica" or the 
"Partnership"), a leading wholesale fuels distributor, today announced that its 
General Partner, CST Brands, Inc. (NYSE: CST) has entered into a definitive 
merger agreement with Alimentation Couche-Tard Inc. (TSX: ATD.A ATD.B) 
(&#8220;Couche-Tard&#8221;). Under the terms of the agreement, Couche-Tard will,
through its acquisition of CST, acquire CST&#8217;s interest in CrossAmerica and
associated Incentive Distribution Rights (&#8220;IDRs&#8221;). The transaction 
has been unanimously approved by the Board of Directors of CST and Couche-Tard 
and is subject to the approval of CST&#8217;s shareholders and the receipt of 
regulatory approvals. The transaction is currently expected to close early 
calendar year 2017.</font></div><div style="line-height:150%;padding-
top:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-
family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Upon completion of the CST and Couche-Tard 
merger, CrossAmerica will become part of one of North America&#8217;s largest 
convenience and fuel retailing networks. By combining Couche-Tard&#8217;s U.S. 
dealer network of approximately 700 sites and CrossAmerica&#8217;s network of 
more than 1,000 locations, the combined organization will also be one of the 
largest wholesale fuel distributors in the United States.</font></div><div 
style="line-height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-align:justify;font-
size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Jeremy Bergeron, 
President of CrossAmerica, said, &#8220;This merger creates tremendous 
opportunity for CrossAmerica and its unitholders. We look forward to working 
closely with Couche-Tard to create further value for all investors, while 
capitalizing on the many strengths and best practices each organization brings 
to the table. In the interim, we intend to continue to execute on our strategy 
of solid growth, while further strengthening our balance sheet and coverage 
ratio.&#8221;</font></div><div style="line-height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-
align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;">&#8220;With its strong acquisition record, CrossAmerica brings 
additional options to Couche-Tard&#8217;s growth strategy and we anticipate 
unlocking additional value with the new relationship,&#8221; stated Brian 
Hannasch, Couche-Tard&#8217;s President and Chief Executive 
Officer.</font></div><div style="line-height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-
align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">About CrossAmerica Partners LP</font></div><div 
style="line-height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-align:justify;font-
size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">CrossAmerica
Partners is a leading wholesale distributor of motor fuels and owner and lessor 
of real estate used in the retail distribution of motor fuels.&#160;Its general 
partner, CrossAmerica GP LLC, is a wholly owned subsidiary of CST Brands, Inc., 
one of the largest independent retailers of motor fuels and convenience 
merchandise in North America.&#160; Formed in 2012, CrossAmerica Partners LP is 
a distributor of branded and unbranded petroleum for motor vehicles in the 
United States and distributes fuel to more than 1,180 locations and owns or 
leases more than 800 sites. With a geographic footprint covering 29 states, the 
Partnership has well-established relationships with several major oil brands, 
including ExxonMobil, BP, Shell, Chevron, Sunoco, Valero, Gulf, Citgo, Marathon 
and Phillips 66. CrossAmerica Partners ranks as one of ExxonMobil&#8217;s 
largest distributors by fuel volume in the United States and in the top 10 for 
additional brands. For additional information, please visit </font><font 
style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;text-
decoration:underline;">www.crossamericapartners.com</font><font style="font-
family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-
height:150%;padding-top:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font 
style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Important 
Additional Information</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-
top:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-
family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">In connection with the proposed transaction, CST
intends to file a proxy statement and other relevant documents concerning the 
proposed transaction with the SEC. The definitive proxy statement will be sent 
or given to CST stockholders and will contain 
</font></div><div><br></div><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-
size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div><div
style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-
size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><div><br></div><div style="line-
height:120%;padding-top:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font 
style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">important information about the 
proposed transaction. INVESTORS AND SECURITY HOLDERS ARE URGED TO READ CAREFULLY
AND IN THEIR ENTIRETY THE PROXY STATEMENT AND ANY OTHER RELEVANT DOCUMENTS FILED
WITH THE SEC, AS WELL AS ANY AMENDMENTS OR SUPPLEMENTS TO THOSE DOCUMENTS, WHEN 
THEY BECOME AVAILABLE. Investors and security holders will be able to obtain a 
copy of the proxy statement as well as other documents filed with the SEC free 
of charge at the SEC&#8217;s website at http://www.sec.gov. In addition, the 
proxy statement, the SEC filings that will be incorporated by reference in the 
proxy statement and the other documents filed with the SEC by CST may be 
obtained free of charge from CST&#8217;s Investor Relations page on its 
corporate website at http://www.cstbrands.com. </font></div><div style="line-
height:120%;padding-top:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font 
style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Certain Information
Concerning Participants</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-
top:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-
family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">CST and its directors, executive officers, and 
certain other members of management and employees may be deemed to be 
participants in the solicitation of proxies from CST stockholders in connection 
with the proposed transaction. Information about the directors and executive 
officers of CST is set forth in CST&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the 
year ended December 31, 2015 and the proxy statement on Schedule 14A for 
CST&#8217;s 2015 Annual Meeting of Stockholders, which was filed with the SEC on
April 29, 2016. Additional information regarding participants in the proxy 
solicitation may be obtained by reading the proxy statement regarding the 
proposed transaction when it becomes available.</font></div><div style="line-
